{{Infobox rail line |name = Gardena Ronda Express |image =Gardena_Ronda_Express.JPG |image_width = |caption = |type = passenger |system = |status = working |start = Ruacia |end = Tschisles |stations = 2 |open = December 22, 2004 |close = |owner = |operator = |character = |stock = |linelength = {{convert|1.24|km|abbr=on}} |tracklength = | tracks = |gauge = {{RailGauge|1200mm|lk=on}} | electrification = yes |speed = {{convert|36|km/h|abbr=on}} |elevation = }}
The '''Gardena Ronda Express''' is a [[funicular]] situated in the [[Val Gherdëina]] near [[Santa Cristina Gherdëina]], connecting the Col Raiser lifts to the Sasslong/Ruacia and Ciampinoi lifts in northern [[Italy]].
== Trains == Two funiculars operate on the system. Both were built by [[Gangloff AG|Gangloff]], and the cable system was manufactured by [[Leitner Ropeways]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.leitner-ropeways.com/en/company/references/if-val-gardena-ronda-express-588/| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180620124859/https://www.leitner-ropeways.com/en/company/references/if-val-gardena-ronda-express-588/| archivedate=June 20, 2018 |title=IF Val Gardena Ronda Express |website=Leitner AG }}</ref> The funicular trains each have four seating cabins capable of seating around 10 and standing around 25. The total capacity is 140 people per train. The trains are {{convert|15.5|m|ftin|frac=8|abbr=on}} long and {{convert|2.3|m|ftin|frac=8|abbr=on}} wide, and weigh {{convert|15,500|kg|lb|abbr=on|sigfig=3}}.
== Track == The whole line runs in a tunnel, which connects two [[gondola lift]]s and through them two [[ski resort]]s. The maximum speed is {{convert|36|km/h|mph|abbr=on}} and the slope is 100[[Per mil|‰]] (10[[%]]). 2000 persons can be transported per hour from one terminus to the other.
== History == Planning started in 1990 and after some changes on the track to avoid buildings, construction started in 2003. With the line's opening in 2004, after nearly forty years without a railway (the [[Val Gardena Railway]] was closed in 1960), the valley has a train again.
