{{Infobox person | name = Yury Konstantinovich Artsybushev | image = Artsybushev.jpg | native_name = Юрий Константинович Арцыбушев | native_name_lang = ru | birth_date = 28 March 1877 | birth_place = Moscow | death_date = 12 November 1952 | death_place = Paris | nationality = Russian | occupation = Artist, Author, Journalist }}
'''Yury Konstantinovich Artsybushev''' ({{lang-ru|Юрий Константинович Арцыбушев}}) (1877–1952) was a [[Russia|Russian]] [[artist]], [[author]], and [[journalist]]. <ref>[http://www.elar.ru/projekt/garf.html elar.ru] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070403130848/http://www.elar.ru/projekt/garf.html |date=April 3, 2007 }}</ref> Artsybushev served as the [[Chief editor|chief editor]] of the [[satirical magazine]] ''Zritel'' (Spectator)<ref>[http://collection.ng.ru/collect/2001-01-10/7_ulynovsk.html collect.ng.ru] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929131048/http://collection.ng.ru/collect/2001-01-10/7_ulynovsk.html|date=September 29, 2007}}</ref> and as an organizer of the Theater of Miniatures in [[Moscow]].<ref>[http://www.russiandvd.com/store/person.asp?id=6846&media=6&type=actor&genreid=&fullbiography=1 russianDVD.com] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927214247/http://www.russiandvd.com/store/person.asp?id=6846&media=6&type=actor&genreid=&fullbiography=1 |date=September 27, 2007 }}</ref> He is known for his live sketches of Russian [[politicians]] and [[Revolutionaries|revolutionaries]] including those of [[Vladimir Lenin]] and [[Leon Trotsky]] from the [[Russian Constituent Assembly]] in [[Petrograd]].
